      },
      "date": "2012-10-14 17:06:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nYes, move target.c and maybe ldlm_lib.c in one patch, the do function renaming in a separate patch vthe reason is that git detects file renames by how similar the files are, but if too many changes are made across the move they are considered separate files and history is lost. \n\nYou could see if \"git log lustre/target/*.c\" showed all of the history for target.c. If yes then the current patch is ok, but I'd think that Gerrit would have shown this as a rename...",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
